    "wf": {
      "behavior_spec_summary": "The oracle emits wellformedness results inside the pretty-printed theory, wrapped in a block comment: `/* All wellformedness checks were successful. */` on success, or `/*\\nWARNING: the following wellformedness checks failed!\\n\\n<blocks>\\n*/` on failure. Each block = topic header + a `=`-underline exactly as long as the topic (counting significant leading/trailing spaces) + blank line + body; blocks joined by blank lines. I enumerated 13 distinct warning topics in a fixed canonical order: (1) Unbound variables, (2) Public constants with mismatching capitalization, (3) Variable with mismatching sorts or capitalization, (4) Reserved names, (5) Fr facts must only use a fresh- or a msg-variable, (6) Special facts, (7) Fact arity issues, (8) Fact multiplicity issues, (9) Facts occur in the left-hand-side but not in any right-hand-side (trailing space), (10) Formula terms, (11) Formula guardedness (leading space), (12) Nat Sorts, (13) Subterm Convergence Warning — plus (14) Message Derivation / Derivation Checks which the binary appends via Maude and are not AST-derivable. The public-names report (#2) is generated separately and inserted before the first present anchor topic (#3..#13); after_public_names_topics()/insert_wf_before expose that. I reverse-engineered exact byte templates for every topic (trailing-space quirks, `\\n  \\n` 2-space separators, the nested `  Fact `name':` arity/multiplicity layout, the `factName `X' arity: N multiplicity: Linear` LHS/RHS format with a nearest-neighbour suggestion gated at edit-distance <=3), the term pretty-printer (`~x`/`$p`/`x.1`, `<a, b>`, `a^b`, `(a*b)`, `(a++b)`, `(a(+)b)`, `(a%+b)`, `Name( args )` facts), and a single-line unicode formula printer. Key position-dependent finding: reserved facts are {K,KU,KD} on LHS/RHS but {K,KU,KD,In,Out,Fr} in actions; In/Out/Fr misplaced on LHS/RHS are Special facts. Unguarded restrictions and SAPIC unbound process vars are fatal errors, not warnings.",
      "components_done": [
        "Core report API: WfError/WfError::new, WfReport, topics(), underline_topic(), render_report() byte-identical comment + success line, insert_wf_before(), after_public_names_topics()",
