      "behavior_spec_summary": "The graph payload is graphviz DOT served at /thy/trace/N/interactive-graph-def/proof/... (intdot is a fixed HTML shell embedding <dot-graph-viz dotsrc=...>; a --with-json backend exists but is unavailable and absent from the corpus, so JSON graph format is unobserved). DOT uses SIMPLE header for pure multiset-rewriting graphs and COMPACT/clustered header (packmode=cluster, compound=true, subgraph cluster_<Role>_Session_<k>). Trigger byte-verified over all 14705 graphs, zero violations: compact iff a node has role != Undefined. Three node shapes: record (rule instances, label {{prem}|{info}|{concl}} with <nK> ports, per-rule fillcolor, role), ellipse (knowledge/action/temporal, optional color), plain (legend HTML TABLE). Edges nS[:port] -> nD[:port][attrs] with observed style vocabulary (red/dashed KU, bold weight-10 structural, blue3/dashed temporal, invis legend). Abbreviation NAME=PREFIX+counter, PREFIX = first two alphabetic chars uppercased of the root symbol name (function; unquoted constant; undecorated variable; or operator function name: ^=exp=EX, *=mult=MU, ++=union=UN, xor=XO); nests bottom-up (EX1='g'^MU1). Legend rows NAME = EXPANSION, continuation rows hang-indented 65 spaces (= TABLE tag width), expansions HTML-escaped. No exposed simplification level (URL query params inert; no CLI flag). Validated end-to-end: parser ingests every captured payload into the crate model and re-serialization reproduces 14705/14705 byte-exact.",
